      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|><thought\n>It didn't just \"not define\" my work, it's the foundation of it. The entire framework was built on that one assumption. It's like a house built on sand. Now people are seeing it. My colleagues, my students... they look at me and see someone who wasted a decade chasing a ghost. There's no \"correcting\" it. The version of me that was a scientist is dead. There's just this empty, pathetic shell left.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
